pho (0.9.8) unstable; urgency=low
  * Add -p resolution option, for use with projectors.
  * -c now allows custom specification of caption/comment file.
  * Contributions from david <somloieater@gmail.com> Sun, 8 Apr 2011 11:15:00 +0200
 -- Akkana Peck <akkana@shallowsky.com>  Mon, 3 Sep 2012 19:27:00 -0800

pho (0.9.7) unstable; urgency=low
  * Add ability to add new image files or change the list without restarting.
  * Reorganize some scaling options.
  * More configurable PHO_CMD variable.
  * Allow up to 31 notes flags.
  * Swap meanings of f and F.
  * Lots of code cleanup and reliability fixes.
  * add .cap file support for captions - read into comment field
    and saved on exit
  * Contributions from david <somloieater@gmail.com> Sun, 8 Apr 2011 11:15:00 +0200
 -- Akkana Peck <akkana@shallowsky.com>  Mon, 3 Sep 2012 19:27:00 -0800

pho (0.9.6) unstable; urgency=low

  * Add Keyword mode.
  * Add slideshow mode.
  * Swap -f and -F.
  * Add PHO_CMD environment variable.
  * Simplify exif/Makefile so it'll work on FreeBSD and other systems where make is non-GNU make.
  * Change the list next/prev code to fix (I hope) a bug where pho would get confused and cycle from the last image back to the first.
  * Lots of performance and stability work.

 -- Akkana Peck <akkana@shallowsky.com>  Sun, 9 Nov 2008 16:20:00 -0800

pho (0.9.5) unstable; urgency=low

  * Code cleanup: rewrote the image list handling to use a linked list.
  * Port to gtk2, and build under either gtk1 or gtk2.
  * Add new "fullscreen mode" (e.g. for presentations, or for difficult
    window managers).
  * Add handling of PHO_ARGS environment variable
  * Added a workaround for Metacity's evil window size handling.
  * Lots of bug fixes.

 -- Akkana Peck <akkana@shallowsky.com>  Mon, 20 Mar 2007 21:25:00 -0800

pho (0.9.2) unstable; urgency=low

  * Don't try to move the window unless the image size has changed
    (fix the annoying bug where pho wouldn't let you move windows).
  * Fix a crash after dismissing the info dialog by clicking
    on the windowmanager "X".

 -- Akkana Peck <akkana@shallowsky.com>  Tue, 30 Sep 2003 23:24:01 -0800

pho (0.9.1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Rusty Russell: fix an off-by-one error in rotation code,
    eliminating the need to allocate more memory than needed.
  * Brian Langenberger: bracket printed filenames with quotes if
    they contain spaces or quote characters.

